place.name: ASHMANHAUGH
place.gazetteerText: ASHMANHAUGH, a parish in Tunstead district, Norfolk; 9 miles NNE of Norwich r. station. Post town, Coltishall under Norwich. Acres, 665. Real pro perty, £1,172. Pop., 136. Houses, 32. The property is divided between two. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £42. Patron, Sir J. H. Preston, Bart. The church is good. Charities, £12. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
